text: Jutta Pauliina Urpilainen (born 4 August 1975) is a Finnish politician. She was the first female chair of the Social Democratic Party of Finland, which she led from 2008 to 2014. She was the Minister of Finance as well as the Deputy Prime Minister of Finland from 2011 to 2014. She is the European Commissioner for International Partnerships since 2019. She is a candidate for President of Finland in the 2024 election. ==References== Category:1975 births Category:Living people Category:Deputy Prime Ministers of Finland Category:European Union politicians
